<br>
I always thought it was obvious that in a pick-up group, even with evade, you have to work the aggro range with no backstabs at first just to get a feel for the main tank's taunt-ability.<br>
<br>
Sort of like diving a different car with a manual transmission, you just have to start of slowly until you find out where the sweet spot is on the clutch ... you don't just go go go <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utaradinsoulcaller.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taradin Soulcaller</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 12:12:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Nekoken, I have to agree with everything you said.</span><hr size=1> Hey all I have been reading through the thread and wanted to bring up the fact that the mobs you are fighting -should- have an effect on whether or not evade works.  The DPS that we output is always going to place us near the top of the hate list, it is a given.  Timing, distance, procs, and other management tools are going to help, but in my experience it completely depends on what mobs I am fighting as to my success rate on evade.. Example: Campin XP in velks @ frenzy I evade bout 80 percent of the time. Agro turns, drop it back to the tank NP. However when raiding in ToV I successfully evade bout 20-30 percent of the time. Might the mob you are fighting have an influence on your successrate? I think it does.<br>
