<br>
FD takes you out of combat longer then jolt or evade....and it gets resisted.<br>
<br>
IMO the aggro management tools handed to these three classes is about right.  You shouldnt be able massive amounts of DPS without some trade off and use of skill.  <br>
<br>
Good tanks should be a much better way to assure taking no aggro then a successful skill or a spell.<br>
<br>
Also someone mention of getting a successful evade message without shedding agro....wanted to add that happens quite a bit with Jolt as well.  Text says spell landed but mob keeps beating on ya. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utobyl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tobyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 4:35:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=41>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: about right</span><hr size=1> Distance is a factor that is more important on some mobs than others.  Example, skeleton mobs in the crypt in Seb.  95% of the agro off these is entirely proximity.  You can succeed every evade, turn attack off, beg for mercy, whatever, but if you dont move back from the mob you will get pasted.  So as for &quot;failed&quot; evades when getting a successful message, yes its very possible to evade and still have agro.  Sometimes you are just plain that high up on the list.  It also depends how well taunt works on the mob, etc.  These factors vary from mob to mob.<br>
<br>
I dont know that I agree that delay affects agro all that much.  Maybe a little but certainly not to any great extent.  Most warriors are now claiming that 2hs is out-taunting their dual wields, procs aside.  I myself used FESS and CoL for quite a while (17 dly mainhand, 18 offhand with 41% haste) and never noticed any significant agro increase over say Rage and RSSS (25 and 26 dly) even though I was hitting MUCH more and doing quite a bit more damage.<br>
