From a Rogues stand point, with our Evade skill, this is not true.  It's  coded that when we have a successful evade, that we drop between the 2nd and 3rd position on the hate list or 500 points, which ever is greater.  Which means that from Verants own words, there should never be a successful-failed evade.  (Assuming that the mob isn't rooted, or proximity agro, etc) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukarak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 6:47:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: about right</span><hr size=1> There is more to aggro than just the hate list.  Evade affects the hate list.  Therefore, although evade has a substantial effect on aggro, it is not a sole determining factor. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvagabond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vagabond</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/02 8:19:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23086.topic&index=44>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: about right</span><hr size=1> This might be taken as flamish, but I don't mean it to be.<br>
<br>
Those of us that are talking about evade not being effective enough at once every 10 sec arn't just 5th lvl twinks or the like.  And we all know the _workarounds_ for evade failing.  We know about undead aggro, root aggro, etc.<br>
<br>
The person that mentioned the RNG hit it right on the head. IF VI didn't have such a crappy RNG then evade would problably be fine.  66%ish chance of succeeding is fine using any weapon combination out there, assuming your tank has comperable (and really, on raid situations, your MT always has comperable or better) weaponry IF you don't get a bad RNG seed.<br>
<br>
But VI's RNG sucks. And so we deal with evade fail after fail.  We turn off attack (often before we even get aggro), we back off.  We watch our DPS plummet.  And when we finally get a success, we wade back into the fight.<br>
<br>
The other day in an exp group, I failed evade _6_ times in a row.  Not interupted, but pure fails.  Now, this was exp, and the cleric simply chealed me after the mob and didn't think anything of it.  But the odds, given a real RNG, of someone failing evade 6 times in a row? 1:729. And no, failing 6 times in a row is not a 1 in 729 attempts event for me.<br>
<br>
If only I could find a casino that used VI's RNG, I'd be rich in very short order.<br>
<br>
Ninen of Saryrn<br>
